cast.overview: Inspired by her mom's rebellious past and a confident new friend, a shy 16-year-old publishes an anonymous zine calling out sexism at her school.
cast.title: Moxie

details.biography: Alycia Pascual-Peña is a New York native and Spanish bilingual who began her entertainment career at the young age of three years old. After performing in SHINE's acting, dancing, modeling, and singing showcases, Alycia instantly became a successful quadruple threat. She began modeling for brands such as Neiman Marcus, JC Penny, Belks, and became the face of Hearts for Hearts Dolls. After much success in the modeling industry, Alycia began commercial work for Telemundo, Univision, and later experienced her television debut in NBC's "Chase" and Gregory Allen Howard's "The Plug". Alycia's passion for the arts is matched by her drive for positivity, as she spends her time being involved in a plethora of community building organizations. Alycia is destined to become one of the nation's top performers.
details.name: Alycia Pascual-Peña
